## 🧠 What I Learnt – Detailed Reflections from the Hands-On Work

- Acquiring images properly (E01 with hash verification) is critical — one mistake and the entire chain of custody is broken.
- Autopsy’s timeline view is incredibly powerful; seeing the exact sequence of attacker actions made the incident feel real.
- Volatility revealed artefacts that disk analysis missed (injected code, network connections that had already closed).
- Writing the report while the evidence was fresh produced a much higher quality document.
- Developing playbooks taught me that good response is not just technical — it requires clear, actionable steps that a team can follow under pressure.

This project has given me tangible experience in the investigation side of cyber defence that I can discuss confidently in any selection process.

